    <h3>Sieve of Eratosthenes</h3>
    <p>To find all primes up to n: list 2 through n, then cross out multiples of 2 (keeping 2), multiples of 3 (keeping 3), and so on. Whatever remains is prime. You only need to sieve up to the square root of n.</p>

